    "body": "### Problem\n\nPutting extmark on second cell of double width character can result into rendering issues if later some other highlighting update is done.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following config file:\r\n```lua\r\n-- Create helper functions\r\nlocal ns_id = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test')\r\n\r\n_G.add_extmark = function()\r\n  local opts = { virt_text = { { 'a', 'Search' } }, virt_text_win_col = 9, virt_text_pos = 'overlay' }\r\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns_id, 0, 0, opts)\r\nend\r\n\r\n_G.add_match = function() vim.cmd([[match Comment /\\k\\+/]]) end\r\n\r\n_G.clear_extmarks = function() vim.api.nvim_buf_clear_namespace(0, ns_id, 0, -1) end\r\n\r\n-- Set up buffer with double width characters\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'このアニメーションは' })\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Start Neovim with `nvim --clean -u <path/to/config/file.lua>`.\r\n3. `:lua add_extmark()`. Should properly put extmark on the second cell of double width character.\r\n4. `:lua add_match()`. It shifts the extmark by one cell making it a separate cell while last double width character can not be reached with cursor.\r\n5. `:lua clear_extmark()`. Has no effect on rendered text.\r\n6. `:call clearmatches()`. Everything is back to normal.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPlacing extmark into second cell of double width character with `virt_text_win_col` should not cause rendering issues.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2048+g367e52cc7, but could reproduce all the way to 0.6.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (doesn't have this functionality)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.6.10-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9, wezterm 20230408-112425-69ae8472, kitty 0.25.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color, xterm-256color, xterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
